The paper proposes a new framework for sparse coding that enhances learning robustness, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of this framework in signal processing applications, which suggests that it may fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) or information theory (cs.IT) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of self-paced learning, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.NE). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
